(Procedural Icicle Project - Report Structure) Tj T*
(============================================) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(1. Title / Project Overview) Tj T*
(===========================) Tj T*
(Title suggestion:) Tj T*
(Procedural Icicle Scene in OpenGL) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Shortly explain:) Tj T*
(- You built a procedural icy ceiling scene.) Tj T*
(- Icicles are generated in code, not modeled manually.) Tj T*
(- The scene uses OpenGL, shaders, procedural mesh generation, normals, lighting, alpha blending,) Tj T*
(  and a textured background.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(2. Motivation) Tj T*
(=============) Tj T*
(Explain why you chose this project:) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(I chose procedural icicle generation because it combines mesh generation, randomness, lighting,) Tj T*
(normals, and scene composition. The goal was to create a visually recognizable ice cave scene) Tj T*
(while learning low-level OpenGL concepts.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(3. Problem Statement) Tj T*
(====================) Tj T*
(Example:) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(The goal of the project was to generate many icicles procedurally within the dimensions of a) Tj T*
(roof plane, render them with lighting, and compose them with a background image to create an ice) Tj T*
(cave scene.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Mention what you wanted to achieve visually:) Tj T*
(- Icicles attached to a roof) Tj T*
(- Random variation in height, radius, shape, and lean) Tj T*
(- Non-overlapping placement) Tj T*
(- Lighting that makes the geometry readable) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(4. Implementation Details) Tj T*
(=========================) Tj T*
(This should be the largest section.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Suggested subsections:) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(OpenGL Setup) Tj T*
(Explain:) Tj T*
(- window/context using ituGL) Tj T*
(- VAO, VBO, EBO) Tj T*
(- indexed drawing) Tj T*
(- depth testing) Tj T*
(- blending) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Procedural Geometry) Tj T*
(Explain your vertex format:) Tj T*
(Each vertex stores position and normal:) Tj T*
(x, y, z, nx, ny, nz) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Explain how one icicle is generated:) Tj T*
(- one tip vertex) Tj T*
T*
(Page 1 / 3) Tj
ET
